A towering, serpentine dragon made entirely of dense programming code characters, coiling upward through a misty bamboo forest. The dragon's body transitions from compact, elegant segments near its head to an impossibly long, tangled mass of loops and knots trailing far below. Japanese kanji symbols float like fireflies around the creature, some trying to weave into the code-dragon's scales but unable to fit. The scene is bathed in soft golden afternoon light filtering through the bamboo, with the dragon appearing both majestic and unwieldy, struggling under its own excessive length. Studio Ghibli style with rich watercolor textures, whimsical atmosphere, and careful attention to the interplay of nature and the digital creature.
